  = must: classify the untracked project slice by role
  = must: keep ignored runtime surfaces outside source authority
  = must: report test result before calling the worktree runnable
  = must: decide whether the next lead is commit preparation, source/spec indexing, math-tool audit, or whole-field synthesis
  = must: keep local branch conclusions subordinate to whole-field RH objects
  - never: claim commit integrity before staging and committing
  - never: treat green tests as mathematical truth, RH evidence, or proof readiness

& [WorktreeIntegrityReviewSJS] is the specification justification trace
  + [processed_stage_set] is source_preserved, delineated, canonicalized, constraint_checked, justified, and review_scoped
  + [processing_result] is accepted_worktree_review_contract
  + [reasoning_result] is the untracked project has enough coherent source/spec/analysis/tool/test material to review as a project slice, but not enough Git authority to call it committed work

(worktree_integrity_review) :repo-first review: /HEAD to WORKTREE, roles, ignored runtime, tests, next lead/ |RH evidence|
  + [inside] is worktree role classification, test result, review findings, and next route
  + [boundary] is pre-commit project integrity only
  |outside| proof, disproof, zero certification, commit integrity before commit, and hidden authority
